synonyms.synonym: Sequence like an intermediate conductance potassium channel subunit
Sodium and chloride-activated ATP-sensitive potassium channel Slo2.1

protein.general_function: Involved in calcium-activated potassium channel activity
protein.specific_function: Outward rectifying potassium channel. Produces rapidly activating outward rectifier K(+) currents. Activated by high intracellular sodium and chloride levels. Channel activity is inhibited by ATP and by inhalation anesthetics, such as isoflurane. Inhibited upon stimulation of G-protein coupled receptors, such as CHRM1 and GRIA1

reference.reference_text: Bhattacharjee A, Joiner WJ, Wu M, Yang Y, Sigworth FJ, Kaczmarek LK: Slick (Slo2.1), a rapidly-gating sodium-activated potassium channel inhibited by ATP. J Neurosci. 2003 Dec 17;23(37):11681-91.
